cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a new routing protocol for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a clustering-based approach for optimum functionality which falls under the subfield of distributed computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of different approaches based upon clustering for enhancing network life-time which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions fault-tolerant monitoring which is related to security and cryptography in WSNs. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new protocol for enhancing stability period, network life-time, and throughput which falls under the subfield of systems and control.
